description: Seonyudo Park is located in Seoul. It has a nursery, a pond full of lilies, and an exhibition hall. It is very beautiful.

The Korea Embroidery Museum was established in 1976 and is a specialized museum for embroidery. The museum currently preserves about 1,000 pieces of embroidery from the Joseon Dynasty. You can see all kinds of beautiful Hanbok and screens, etc. The exhibition is very gorgeous, and there is also a try-on area. After the visit, if you are interested, you can pay to attend the lecture and learn embroidery. The cost of the embroidery experience is 3,000 won. With the lecturer's explanation and demonstration for about an hour, you can embroider the handkerchief yourself and take it home. However, all lectures are in Korean, so it is better to have a tour guide or translator.
